The racing to beat another group, the arguments afterwards, the obligatory post on the Rants and Flames post just leave me feeling ill and tired.<br>
<br>
I like to hang out with my friends and joke about fireman porn, I like to try to accomplish fun things with bad odds (Neriad Mistress without a cleric, piece of cake!).  I don't like to argue, fight or race to a spawn.<br>
<br>
I don't know if the heart of the issue lies with us or with the game design, but the way we are often pitted against each other for pixels makes me think of mad scientists watching rats scurrying through a maze after cheese.<br>
<br>
Sorry for the rambling reflection.  There is no way to create a &quot;kindler gentler Norrath.&quot;  There is no way to regulate rotations for every desired spawn.  I'm going to work harder at trying to respect what other guilds are doing and will encourage my guild to do the same.  <br>
<br>
Gloriana Frostglitter<br>
Oracle<br>
